,Recommended,249190,14546550,"Posted: 19 February, 2015",all,unknown14725,"Pretty graphics, but unfortunately useless controls. You can't even change the height/altitude of your vessels. Your vessels are categorized by size (S, M, L, XL, etc) instead of function, so it's impossible to distinguish between the different classes of spacecraft (corvettes, cruisers, carriers, fighters, etc) in your armada. All the icons are more or less identical, and you have to keep clicking through your armada until you find the one you're looking for. Some interesting concepts, but it's really far away to even match the essence of the Homeworld games. The game lacks any feeling of maneuvering ""real"" spaceships. There's no inertia, vector thrusting, or even moving parts like cannons. The ships just flip around with no inertia and start moving towards their destination. And ion beams and lasers don't even emerge from the space vessels themselves. It's fun to play a few of hours, but then you get bored, and just select all your spaceships and right click the enemy to get it over with. Would never buy it at full price. Wait for at least 50% sale. It's worth a few bucks if you just want to kill a few hours of boredom."
