76561197963802201,Recommended,249190,12511356,"Posted: 16 October, 2014",all,Aramada,"Ancient Space tries very hard to appeal to Homeworld fans, and i'd say it does a decently successful job. Instead of comparing this title to the 1st Homeworld, a better comparison would be Cataclysm or Homeworld 2 due to very strict unit caps.This might seem like a horrible thing, but it actually is a saving grace for this game. Each and every single ship so far has some sort of special ability (sometimes two) which can be triggered at specific times for great effect. The more ships you add from the current values when having this variety in individual ships creates a micromanagement hell. It strikes an excellent balance between fleet size and interactivity of each type of ship.This game has its problems for sure, but if you're looking for that Homeworld kick, you will find it here. Just don't expect it to come close to the gem that is its source material."
