76561198045291203,Recommended,249190,16148351,"Posted: 2 June, 2015",all,ensignedwards,"My only complaint about this game is that it is at times challenging to the point of frustration even on the lowest difficulty setting. For this reason, I would not recommend it to those who are not already familiar with the RTS genre.That issue aside, this is a very good game that I would strongly recommend to RTS fans. It's a fairly old school experience that reminded me of the original StarCraft and the old Dune games, but while it's not especially innovative, it's not blindly clinging to the past, either, and it has enough modern ideas and mission diversity to not feel like retread of old games. It's an homage to the RTS greats of the past, but not an attempt to ape them.The story is pretty strong -- though suffering slightly due to technical limitations -- and the soundtrack is one of the best I've heard. Ambience is something RTS games tend to struggle with, but Ancient Space does a wonderful job of making you feel isolated and alone in a vast and often hostile universe.Plus it has Phlox in it.All in all, a game more than worth its minimal price tag."
